p: Clade identification was performed using R v3.4.3 [ 19], and a NSW-specific HIV-1 clade was defined as a node on the CRF01_AE phylogeny in which at least 80% of all tips were NSW sequences collected in this study [ 14, 20, 21]. ClusterPicker v1.2.5. [ 22] was used to identify potential active transmission clusters with that where characterized by a node support of 0.9 or higher and a genetic distance of 1.5% or lower [ 23, 24].
